<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBE5722FF6894EE7C6B0560" blockId="15.[151,1437,1642,2029]" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBE5722FF6894EE7CDA054D" bold="true" box="[199,433,1786,1812]" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">Soldier and worker</emphasis>
. Described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF83B4DAFFBE5722FDF094EE7E50054D" author="Constantino, R." box="[607,827,1786,1812]" pageId="15" pageNumber="460" pagination="3 - 9" refId="ref8255" refString="Constantino, R. (1990) Two new species of termites (Insecta, Isoptera) from western Brazilian Amazonia. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, Serie Zoologia, 6 (1), 3 - 9." type="journal article" year="1990">Constantino (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, additional pictures of the soldier are provided herein (
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBE5722FF0F950A7D980560" box="[160,243,1822,1849]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1112,1136]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1435,181,1088]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 16. Soldier of Bandeiratermes tellustris (Ibitermes tellustris paratype). a, head in dorsal view; b, in profile." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571709" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571709/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBE5722FF689556784905FD" blockId="15.[151,1437,1642,2029]" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBE5722FF6895567C1B0505" bold="true" box="[199,368,1858,1884]" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">Digestive tube</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBE5722FED095567CB90505" box="[383,466,1858,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1361,1385]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,189,1330]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1436,181,1337]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 17. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes tellustris. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e and f, mixed segment in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571711/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). As described for the genus, the gut conformation is the same as 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBE5722FB02955778230505" authorityName="Emerson" authorityYear="1949" box="[1197,1352,1858,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Armitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="15" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvestrii">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBE5722FB02955778230505" box="[1197,1352,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="460">Ban. silvestrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing only in size (slightly smaller) and by the mesenteric tongue width (slightly wider). We did not have sufficient specimens to prepare the gizzard armature, but the enteric valve is illustrated in the original description.
</paragraph>
